# Online Adaptive Reinforcement Learning with Echo State Networks (ESN-OA)

This repository contains the official implementation of the paper:  
**"Online Adaptive Reinforcement Learning with Echo State Networks for Non-Stationary Dynamics"** *(Accepted at IJCNN)*

## Overview
Deploying Reinforcement Learning (RL) policies in the real world is challenging due to non-stationary dynamics, such as sudden friction changes or external disturbances. 
This repository provides a lightweight online adaptation framework (**ESN-OA**) that integrates an Echo State Network (ESN) with a Soft Actor-Critic (SAC) agent. By updating the readout weights online using Recursive Least Squares (RLS), the agent can rapidly adapt to out-of-distribution (OOD) dynamics in real-time without the need for backpropagation or prior meta-training.

## Requirements
* Python 3.8+
* PyTorch
* Stable-Baselines3
* Gymnasium (with MuJoCo)
* NumPy, Matplotlib

```bash
pip install torch stable-baselines3 gymnasium[mujoco] matplotlib

File Structure & Usage
-----------------------------------
The repository is organized by environments (CartPole and HalfCheetah).

[CartPole]
- train_cartpole.py
  Train the SAC agent and ESN in a stationary environment.

- eval_cartpole.py
  Evaluate the robustness against periodic wind disturbances.

- pretrain_wout_cartpole.py
  Pre-train the ESN readout weights (W_out) using stationary data (for ESN-OA-PT).

- measure_time_cartpole.py
  Measure and compare the inference time (ms) per control step.


[HalfCheetah]
- train_halfcheetah.py
  Train the SAC agent and ESN in a stationary MuJoCo environment.

- eval_halfcheetah.py
  Evaluate the robustness against varying friction coefficients.

- pretrain_wout_halfcheetah.py
  Pre-train the ESN readout weights (W_out).

- plot_reward_transition_halfcheetah.py
  Plot the reward transition when the friction coefficient abruptly changes during an episode (reproduces Fig. 5).

- plot_wout_norm_halfcheetah.py
  Plot the temporal evolution of the ESN output weight update norm (||W_t^out - W_{t-1}^out||) during the friction change (reproduces Fig. 6).


-----------------------------------
Quick Start
-----------------------------------
To train the base model on CartPole:

python train_cartpole.py

## Citation
Aoi Yoshimura and Gouhei Tanaka, Online Adaptive Reinforcement Learning with Echo State Networks for Non-Stationary Dynamics,
*Proceedings of the 2026 International Joint Conference on Neural Networks (accepted)* [arXiv:2602.06326](https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.06326)